tldr: The user requested an evaluation of the codebase against an SOW for a
  sleep questionnaire application, focusing on database implementation, a simple
  dashboard, and middleware. A plan was created and partially implemented to add
  a database for responses, a simple password-protected admin dashboard, and
  update demographic data collection.
overview: The user initiated a project to implement database storage and an
  admin dashboard for a Sleep Questionnaire Application based on a provided
  Statement of Work. After an initial codebase evaluation, it was determined
  that a database for questionnaire responses, CSV export, an admin dashboard,
  and authentication were missing. The user opted for a simple password-based
  authentication system and a combined approach for demographic data collection
  (year of birth, sex, zipcode, weight, height). The implementation began by
  updating the demographic fields in the application's types, validation, and
  form components. A new  model was added to the Prisma
  schema. Subsequently, a lightweight authentication system was built, including
  helper functions for session management using signed cookies and API routes
  for admin login and logout. The next steps involve creating API endpoints for
  questionnaire responses and developing the admin dashboard pages.
